Mozambique’s Nacala Airbase to Cost $110 Million to Convert, Noticias Says

-- B y   F r e d   K a t e r e r e
-- 
2011-04-11T05:44:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/mozambique-s-nacala-airbase-to-cost-110-million-to-convert-noticias-says.html
Odebrecht S.A., a Brazilian
construction and engineering company, said conversion
of  Mozambique ’s Nacala military air base to an international
airport will begin this month, Noticias reported, citing an
unidentified person.  The Maputo-based newspaper said the project will cost an
estimated $110 million and will process 300,000 passengers per
year when completed.  The airport will handle direct flights to
destinations in  Africa ,  Asia  and the Americas, Noticias said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Katerere in Maputo at 
 fkaterere@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Agnes Nikoi at 
 anikoi@bloomberg.net  